European Union policy for disabled people is a policy for all of the disabled people in Europe. In the European Union for the policy towards disabled people are primarily responsible governments of the Member States. This is related to one of the main principles of the functioning of the European Union, known as the principle of subsidiarity, according to which what can be done better at the national level, should be done at the national level. Policy for people with disabilities carried out in different EU countries for many years, was inspired mainly the activities of two international organizations: the Council of Europe and the United Nations. EU based on their achievements during the creation of the current strategy work for people with disabilities.
